  {
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "There is a lot of different type of refinements in the end. \r\nUsing the template.item hook and passing a function that returns a template is totally possible, but because of the multiple filter type `disjunctive`, `numerical` there is a lot of use case to manage, and it doesn't feel as the most efficient way to do it, just in order to display the `attributeName` in addition to the refined value.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.currentRefinedValues({\r\n      container: '#active-filters',\r\n      clearAll: 'after',\r\n      transformData: function(data) {\r\n        console.log(data);\r\n        return data;\r\n      },\r\n      templates: {\r\n        item: function(item) {\r\n          var html = '';\r\n          if (item.type === 'disjunctive' && item.name === 'false') {\r\n            html = '';\r\n          }\r\n          else {\r\n            html = `<span class=\"ais-current-refined-values--attribute-name\">${item.attributeName}</span>: <span class=\"ais-current-refined-values--name\">${item.name}</span> <span class=\"ais-current-refined-values--count\">(${item.count})</span>`;\r\n          }\r\n\r\n          return html;\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    })\r\n  );\r\n```\r\n\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1101220/23455677/bfc2a1a2-fe70-11e6-8159-eaf5228197e8.png)\r\n",
    "created_at": "2017-03-01T10:26:08Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2015#issuecomment-283302718",
    "id": 283302718,
